    Print Method for Summary of Generalized Kumaraswamy Regression Models

    print.summary.gkwreg.Rd

    Formats and prints the output of summary.gkwreg objects, displaying detailed information about a fitted Generalized Kumaraswamy regression model including coefficient tables, significance tests, residuals, and goodness-of-fit statistics.

    # S3 method for class 'summary.gkwreg'
print(
  x,
  digits = max(3, getOption("digits") - 3),
  signif.stars = getOption("show.signif.stars"),
  ...
)

    Arguments

    x

    An object of class "summary.gkwreg", typically the result of calling summary on a gkwreg object.

    digits

    Integer indicating the number of significant digits to display. Default is max(3, getOption("digits") - 3).

    signif.stars

    Logical, if TRUE (default is set by option show.signif.stars), significance stars are printed for coefficients.

    ...

    Additional arguments passed to printCoefmat.

    Value

    The input object x is returned invisibly.

    Details

    This method displays a formatted summary of a GKw regression model in a similar style to glm output. The printed information includes:

    • The model call

    • Summary of deviance residuals (quantiles)

    • Coefficient tables for each parameter (\(\alpha\), \(\beta\), \(\gamma\), \(\delta\), \(\lambda\)) with estimates, standard errors, z-values, and p-values

    • Significance code legend (if significance stars are displayed)

    • Null and residual deviance with degrees of freedom

    • AIC (Akaike Information Criterion)

    • Additional model statistics: log-likelihood, BIC, RMSE, Efron's R2, mean absolute error

    • Cache performance metrics

    • Optimization convergence status and number of iterations

    For each parameter, the print method also shows the associated link function and scale factor. Significance codes follow the standard R convention for p-values.

    See also

    summary.gkwreg for creating summary objects for GKw models.

    gkwreg for fitting Generalized Kumaraswamy regression models.

    printCoefmat for the function used to format coefficient matrices.

    Examples

    if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
# Fit a GKw model
fit <- gkwreg(y ~ x1 | x2 | 1 | 1 | 1, data = my_data)

# Generate and print summary
summary(fit)

# Store summary and customize display
sum_fit <- summary(fit)
print(sum_fit, digits = 4, signif.stars = FALSE)
} # }
